<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12182d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12182d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12182d"> 182(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> BVM thistle ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">To this place Charlotte O&apos;Brien, who loved flowers hardly less even than other live things, came to look for a reported rare plant &ldquo;<mark>The Virgin Mary&apos;s Thistle</mark>&rdquo;, &ldquo;so-called because the leaves are all blotched and marbled with white stains, and legend made it a sacred plant bearing for ever <mark>stains of the Blessed Virgin&apos;s milk</mark>&rdquo;. <small> Stephen Gwynn, <a name="SGWM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SGWM"><cite title="source">Munster</cite></a> (1911) 61-2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
